1. Building
Run 'make' in the root directory

2. Structure (after make)
- bin : Binary file mksocket
- src : Source file
- build : Object file
- tools : Python program that sends DGRAM packet to socket and BASH program that sends stream to socket (via 'logger')

3. Usage
Run 'mksocket --help', which will print the following:

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Usage: mksocket [OPTION...] SOCKET - Name and path to the socket

mksock -- A program to create a socket and print in terminal everything that is
sent to it.

  -f, --follow               Keep the socket open and output all data sent to
                             it                                                                                              
  -s, --stream               Connect socket as a stream instead of datagram                                                  
                             (default)                                                                                       
  -?, --help                 Give this help list                                                                             
      --usage                Give a short usage message
  -V, --version              Print program version

Report bugs to <henrik.holm@me.com>.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
